The ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has expressed saddeness over the death of its immediate-past National Vice Chairman (North Central), Alhaji Zakari Abdullahi Idde, who died in a fatal car crash. The APC National Publicity Secretary, Malam Lanre Issa-Onilu, said in a statement issued in Abuja that  a minute silence was observed in his honour at the meeting of the party’s National Working Committee (NWC) yesterday. Issa-Onilu said the NWC had sent a delegation to the family of the former National Vice Chairman to deliver the party’s condolences. The party, which expressed condolences to his immediate family, the government and people of Nasarawa State, prayed that Almighty Allah granted the late Alhaji Zakari Idde who was until his death, the Board Chairman of the Lower Niger River Basin Development Authority al-Jannatul Firdausi. APC loses CSO We were not expel by the APC NWC, says Balogun-Fulani APC nullifies suspension of North-East National Vice Chairman